data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` tree **won't compile**. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// EF Core 10
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All that expression-tree plumbing is no longer needed — `SetPropertyCalls` now uses `Action<>` instead of `Expression<Func<>>`.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes that generate migrations

**a) Duplicate property names are uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF 10 will append a number to disambiguate column names. **b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both changes generate rename migrations. **Fix:** pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL safe for logging
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logs (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the same parameter to every other method in the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
